# TheraAI — Remaining Backend Technical Roadmap

> **Scope:** Assessments, Appointments, Settings, Therapist Dashboard, Admin Dashboard, Real-time Comms, AI Enhancements, Third-Party Integrations, Data Seeding & Polish.

---

## Phase 1: Core RBAC, Settings, & Assessments Backend
**Priority:** Highest · **Estimated Effort:** ~3-4 days

### 1A. Strict Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

The existing system has 3 roles ([patient](file:///c:/Users/dawoo/Projects/GitHub/TheraAI-FYP-I/backend/app/dependencies/auth.py#147-152), [psychiatrist](file:///c:/Users/dawoo/Projects/GitHub/TheraAI-FYP-I/backend/app/dependencies/auth.py#140-145), [admin](file:///c:/Users/dawoo/Projects/GitHub/TheraAI-FYP-I/backend/app/dependencies/auth.py#133-138)) in the [UserRole](file:///c:/Users/dawoo/Projects/GitHub/TheraAI-FYP-I/backend/app/models/user.py#13-17) enum but enforcement is loose. We need a layered authorization architecture.

**Architecture:**

```
Request → JWT Auth (get_current_user) → Role Guard (require_role) → Endpoint Logic
```

#### [NEW] `backend/app/dependencies/rbac.py`

Create role-guard dependency factories:

```python
from functools import wraps
from fastapi import Depends, HTTPException, status
from ..dependencies.auth import get_current_user
from ..models.user import UserOut, UserRole

def require_role(*allowed_roles: UserRole):
    """Dependency factory — inject into any endpoint to enforce role checks."""
    async def role_checker(current_user: UserOut = Depends(get_current_user)):
        if current_user.role not in [r.value for r in allowed_roles]:
            raise HTTPException(
                status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN,
                detail="Insufficient permissions for this resource"
            )
        return current_user
    return role_checker

# Pre-built guards
require_patient = require_role(UserRole.PATIENT)
require_therapist = require_role(UserRole.PSYCHIATRIST)
require_admin = require_role(UserRole.ADMIN)
require_therapist_or_admin = require_role(UserRole.PSYCHIATRIST, UserRole.ADMIN)
```

**Usage in endpoints:**
```python
@router.get("/my-patients")
async def get_my_patients(user: UserOut = Depends(require_therapist_or_admin)):
    ...
```

**Frontend Enforcement:**
- Update `ProtectedRoute` component to accept [roles](file:///c:/Users/dawoo/Projects/GitHub/TheraAI-FYP-I/backend/app/dependencies/auth.py#110-130) prop (already partially exists).
- SidebarNav conditionally renders links based on `user.role` from [AuthContext](file:///C:/Users/dawoo/Downloads/landing-page-design/hooks/use-auth.tsx#13-20).

