### 1B. Settings Backend

The Settings page currently stores preferences in `localStorage` only. We need server-side persistence.

#### Database Schema — `user_settings` collection

```json
{
  "_id": ObjectId,
  "user_id": "string (ref: users._id)",
  "theme": "light | dark | system",
  "notifications": {
    "email": true,
    "push": true,
    "appointments": true,
    "insights": true
  },
  "privacy": {
    "share_with_therapist": true
  },
  "updated_at": "datetime"
}
```

#### [NEW] `backend/app/models/settings.py`
Pydantic schemas: `UserSettings`, `UserSettingsUpdate`

#### [NEW] `backend/app/services/settings_service.py`
Methods: [get_settings(user_id)](file:///c:/Users/dawoo/Projects/GitHub/TheraAI-FYP-I/backend/app/config.py#125-128), `upsert_settings(user_id, data)`

#### [NEW] `backend/app/api/settings.py`
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/settings` | Get current user settings |
| `PUT` | `/settings` | Update settings (partial updates via `exclude_unset`) |
| `DELETE` | `/settings/account` | Delete user account + all associated data |

**Indexes:** `user_id` (unique)

