### 2B. Therapist Dashboard Backend

Therapist-specific endpoints for managing patients, viewing alerts, and session summaries.

#### [NEW] `backend/app/api/therapist.py`
| Method | Endpoint | Access | Description |
|--------|----------|--------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/therapist/dashboard` | Therapist | Aggregate stats (active patients, weekly sessions, avg rating) |
| `GET` | `/therapist/patients` | Therapist | List assigned patients with latest mood/journal data |
| `GET` | `/therapist/patients/{id}/history` | Therapist | Patient's journal + mood + assessment timeline |
| `GET` | `/therapist/alerts` | Therapist | Patients flagged critical by AI (negative sentiment streaks) |
| `PUT` | `/therapist/profile` | Therapist | Update own therapist profile |
| `POST` | `/therapist/profile` | Therapist | Create therapist profile (first time setup) |

**AI-Powered Alerts:** A background task scans journal entries from the last 48 hours. If a patient has ≥3 consecutive negative sentiments or specific emotion themes (`grief`, `remorse`, `nervousness` at high confidence), they appear in the therapist's alerts panel.

**New Package:** `apscheduler` — for scheduling the periodic alert scan.

```
pip install apscheduler
```

