## Phase 3: Real-Time Communication
**Priority:** High · **Estimated Effort:** ~5-6 days

### 3A. Real-Time Messaging (WebSocket)

**Package:** FastAPI has native WebSocket support. No extra dependency needed.

#### Database Schema — `messages` collection

```json
{
  "_id": ObjectId,
  "conversation_id": "string",
  "sender_id": "string (ref: users._id)",
  "receiver_id": "string (ref: users._id)",
  "content": "string",
  "type": "text | image | file | system",
  "read_at": "datetime | null",
  "created_at": "datetime"
}
```

#### [NEW] `backend/app/api/messaging.py`
| Type | Endpoint | Description |
|------|----------|-------------|
| `WebSocket` | `/ws/chat/{conversation_id}` | Bi-directional real-time messaging |
| `GET` | `/messaging/conversations` | List conversations for current user |
| `GET` | `/messaging/conversations/{id}/messages` | Paginated message history |
| `POST` | `/messaging/conversations` | Start a new conversation (patient↔therapist) |

**WebSocket Authentication:** Parse JWT from query param `?token=xxx` on WebSocket handshake; reject if invalid.

**Architecture:**
```
Client A  ←→  WebSocket Handler  ←→  In-Memory ConnectionManager  ←→  Client B
                    ↓
              MongoDB (persist)
```

**Frontend:** Use native `WebSocket` API or lightweight wrapper `reconnecting-websocket` (npm).

```
npm install reconnecting-websocket
```

---

### 3B. Voice & Video Calls (WebRTC)

**Recommended Stack:**

| Component | Technology | Why |
|-----------|-----------|-----|
| Signaling Server | FastAPI WebSocket | Exchanges SDP offers/answers and ICE candidates |
| Media Transport | WebRTC (browser-native) | Peer-to-peer, no media server needed for 1:1 calls |
| TURN/STUN Server | Metered.ca free tier or Twilio | NAT traversal for users behind firewalls |
| Frontend | `simple-peer` npm package | Simplifies WebRTC peer connection setup |

```
npm install simple-peer
```

#### [NEW] `backend/app/api/webrtc.py`
| Type | Endpoint | Description |
|------|----------|-------------|
| `WebSocket` | `/ws/call/{appointment_id}` | Signaling channel for WebRTC |
| `POST` | `/calls/initiate` | Create a call record, notify both parties |
| `PATCH` | `/calls/{id}/end` | End call, save duration |

**Flow:**
1. Patient clicks "Join Session" on appointment → opens WebSocket to `/ws/call/{apt_id}`
2. Therapist joins the same WebSocket room
3. SDP offer/answer exchanged via WebSocket
4. ICE candidates exchanged via WebSocket
5. Direct peer-to-peer media stream established (no server relay for 1:1)
6. On disconnect, call duration is logged to the appointment record

**Database Schema Addition** to `appointments`:
```json
{
  "call_log": {
    "started_at": "datetime",
    "ended_at": "datetime",
    "duration_seconds": 1845,
    "type": "video | audio"
  }
}
```

